creator: Intellectual Property Office of Singapore
descriptionHtml:
The Intellectual Property Office of Singapore (IPOS) is a statutory board under the Singapore Ministry of Law. IPOS administers the Singapore IP regime and aims to build a Singapore where innovative enterprises use intangible assets to grow.

IPOS Go provides business owners and innovators convenient on-the-go access to key functions available on the IPOS e-services portal (i.e. IP2SG).

Use IPOS Go to:
- Apply for and renew trademark registrations in Singapore*
- Search for similar trademarks and other registrable IPs in Singapore
- Be notified of application status updates and read correspondences from IPOS*
- View and manage portfolio of previous applications*
- Save and retrieve drafts of trademark applications*

* These functions require login using a SingPass or CorpPass account.

To access the full suite of IPOS e-services, please visit https://www.ip2.sg/ on your desktop or laptop.
descriptionShort: Access popular IPOS e-services, including trademark registration and renewal.

appDetails.recentChangesHtml: Enjoy a speedier and more seamless experience with the latest release of IPOS Go! Besides critical bug fixes and performance improvements, this new release also allows users to download reports of similar trademark searches and receive important announcements from IPOS via the app.

title: IPOS Go

creator: Intellectual Property Office of Singapore
descriptionHtml:
IPOS Go is the world's first mobile app for trade mark registration, launched by the Intellectual Property Office of Singapore (IPOS).

IPOS Go provides business owners and innovators with convenient on-the-go access to key IPOS e-services. Users can apply for trade mark and design registrations in under 10 minutes, conduct 4-in-1 brand searches (business names, trade marks, web domains and social media usernames), renew and manage their IP portfolios and receive updates via push notifications.
descriptionShort: Access services including trade mark and design registration, renewal and search

appDetails.recentChangesHtml: This latest version updates the Singpass and Corppass login process. Login using earlier versions will no longer be supported after 30 June 2023.
